etymology.description: Depicts a footprint pointing up -> stylized as 龰
etymology.interpretation: The character 龰 (yù, 'stylized feet') is a pictographic representation of a footprint with the toes pointing upwards. It was stylized over time from its original form and is related to the character 止(止) (zhǐ, 'foot'), which captures the idea of resting a foot, evolved from oracle script depictions with three toes and a sole.
